    <item>
      <title>diff3d: a spot-the-difference game with infinite levels</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/w/v2/news/diff3d/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jun 2026 11:00:00 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/w/v2/news/diff3d/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;We&amp;rsquo;ve been prototyping a casual 3D game we call &lt;strong&gt;diff3d&lt;/strong&gt;: two side-by-side scenes you rotate and zoom to compare, then press and hold to &amp;ldquo;heal&amp;rdquo; each difference back into place until both scenes match.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>A browser-based editor for the Oberheim Matrix 1000</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/w/v2/news/oberheim-matrix1000/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 20 May 2026 11:00:00 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/w/v2/news/oberheim-matrix1000/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The Oberheim Matrix 1000 is a beloved analog synth from 1984 with a famously cryptic front panel — a handful of buttons for a hundred hidden parameters. So we gave it a proper editor that runs entirely in the browser.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
